# pyvanc

A Python library to read VANC (Vertical Ancillary) data, with a special focus on SCTE-104 messages, from MXF video files. This library uses PyAV for interacting with video files and is inspired by the functionality of [libklvanc](https://github.com/stoth68000/libklvanc).

## Features (Planned)

- Open and process MXF files.
- Extract VANC data from video streams.
- Parse SCTE-104 messages from VANC data.
- Provide a simple API for accessing SCTE-104 message content.

## Installation

```bash
pip install pyvanc
# or for development:
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Basic Usage (Conceptual)

```python
from pyvanc import read_scte104_from_mxf

mxf_file_path = "path/to/your/video.mxf"
scte104_messages = read_scte104_from_mxf(mxf_file_path)

for message in scte104_messages:
    print(f"Found SCTE-104 message: {message}")
```

## Development

This project uses `setuptools` for packaging. To install dependencies for development:

```bash
pip install -e .[dev] # Assuming a [project.optional-dependencies] dev group in pyproject.toml
# or simply
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Contributions are welcome! Please open an issue or submit a pull request.
